    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nI'm somewhat new to the TypeScript/node ecosystem, so excuse me if I'm misunderstanding, but shouldn't the `root_dir` for `mdx_analyzer` (and possibly other TypeScript language servers) search for the nearest `typescript.js`?\n\nThe default, at time of writing: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/7af2c37192deae28d1305ae9e68544f7fb5408e1/lua/lspconfig/configs/mdx_analyzer.lua#L12\n\nPersonally, I've overridden the default with something like the following:\n```lua\nlocal lspconfig = require('lspconfig')\nlocal lspconfig_utils = require('lspconfig.util')\n\nlspconfig.mdx_analyzer.setup({\n    root_dir = lspconfig_utils.root_pattern(\n        'node_modules/typescript',\n        '.git',\n        'package.json'\n    ),\n})\n```\n\nI'm not currently set up to develop in any meaningful capacity on any of my personal machines, or else I'd open the PR myself.",
